data.title: The Origins of Electronic Music
data.meta_description: Musica Electronica - Free download as Word Doc (.doc / .docx), PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read online for free. The document provides a history of electronic music from its origins in the 1960s to modern day. It traces the evolution of electronic music styles from progressive rock in the 1960s to synthpop and disco in the 1970s to new wave and dance genres in the 1980s. The 1990s saw the rise of genres like trance and drum and bass and the 2000s brought mainstream popularity to EDM. The internet has also played a key role in spreading electronic music and lowering barriers to entry for new artists. Overall, the document outlines the growth of electronic music over the past 50+ years from niche genre to one of the biggest in the world today.
